       road in Canterlot!

229
00:11:56,782 --> 00:11:57,616
     Should I keep reading?

230
00:11:58,418 --> 00:11:59,350
           Ha, ha, ha!

231
00:12:00,987 --> 00:12:04,855
      Ah, Celestia, since we're
      both a little tired,

232
00:12:04,957 --> 00:12:07,992
    maybe the first thing we
    do shouldn't be.. too wild.

233
00:12:08,094 --> 00:12:09,928
         Exactly what I
          was thinking.

234
00:12:10,730 --> 00:12:14,864
            ZIP LINE...!

235
00:12:22,909 --> 00:12:27,213
 Now every time we have tea, we
 can remember this magical day!

236
00:12:28,815 --> 00:12:31,282
       Well, I'm glad you
        enjoyed yourself.

237
00:12:31,384 --> 00:12:32,917
      But now, we're going
      to do something

238
00:12:33,019 --> 00:12:34,652
    I've always wanted to do,

239
00:12:34,754 --> 00:12:36,921
    but never could, because
     of my night shift!

240
00:12:37,223 --> 00:12:38,456
     Is it another zip-line!?

241
00:12:39,158 --> 00:12:40,024
               ...No.

242
00:12:40,526 --> 00:12:42,826
      It's the post office!

243
00:12:44,263 --> 00:12:45,330
          It is indeed.

244
00:12:46,232 --> 00:12:49,967
   Just think! All the mail in
  Ponyville goes through here!

245
00:12:50,069 --> 00:12:51,535
       Isn't that amazing!?

246
00:12:52,682 --> 00:12:53,382
          [thud]

247
00:12:54,707 --> 00:12:56,507
       One stamp, please!

248
00:12:58,728 --> 00:13:00,728
          [clattering]

249
00:13:07,653 --> 00:13:09,720
          Wait for it.....!

250
00:13:10,422 --> 00:13:12,656
         [watch ticking]

251
00:13:17,563 --> 00:13:19,097
     You didn't need a stamp

252
00:13:19,199 --> 00:13:21,732
     if you were just going
    to give this to me...

253
00:13:21,834 --> 00:13:24,101
        Yes but, <i>I</i> didn't
         give it to you!

254
00:13:24,203 --> 00:13:26,570
   A mailpony took it from me,

255
00:13:26,672 --> 00:13:30,875
 searched to find who it was
 meant for, and gave it to you!

256
00:13:30,977 --> 00:13:33,045
     It's about the PROCESS!

257
00:13:34,247 --> 00:13:37,548
    [echoing] Did you know that
    nopony has ever explored

258
00:13:37,650 --> 00:13:39,383
         the bottom of
         these caverns?

259
00:13:39,485 --> 00:13:41,385
          [animal roar]

260
00:13:41,487 --> 00:13:43,320
         [cracking rock]
          I wonder why...

261
00:13:44,257 --> 00:13:46,690
 I've always wanted to try this!

262
00:13:48,461 --> 00:13:50,227
  Isn't this wonderful, sister?

263
00:13:52,565 --> 00:13:57,635
<i> ♪ There's a lotta little things</i>
  <i> you gotta do in this world ♪</i>

264
00:13:57,837 --> 00:14:03,007
    <i> ♪ There's a lotta little</i>
    <i> things you oughta view ♪</i>

265
00:14:03,109 --> 00:14:08,212
  <i> ♪ And our little lotta lists</i>
   <i> may be a little bit long ♪</i>

266
00:14:08,314 --> 00:14:13,017
       <i> ♪ And might take a</i>
      <i> lotta bother to do ♪</i>

267
00:14:13,219 --> 00:14:18,356
     <i> ♪ But I'm sure it gets</i>
      <i> better, later on ♪</i>

268
00:14:18,458 --> 00:14:23,828
      <i> ♪ And after darkest</i>
     <i> night's, a new dawn ♪</i>

269
00:14:23,930 --> 00:14:26,530
       <i> ♪ It's my turn to</i>
       <i> do the choosing ♪</i>

270
00:14:26,632 --> 00:14:29,000
 <i> ♪ After river rapid cruising ♪</i>

271
00:14:29,102 --> 00:14:34,237
     <i> ♪ This adventure isn't</i>
     <i> too fun to be..... on ♪</i>

272
00:14:35,074 --> 00:14:39,010
        <i> ♪ [busy music] ♪</i>

273
00:14:39,112 --> 00:14:40,879
       Princess Twilight!

274
00:14:41,381 --> 00:14:43,681
  It has come to our attention
  that you don't intend

275
00:14:43,783 --> 00:14:46,851
   to serve watercress at the
   Royal Swanifying Ceremony.

276
00:14:47,353 --> 00:14:49,353
    There's not enough in
    the castle kitchens to--

277
00:14:49,855 --> 00:14:52,322
    Don't tell me. Tell him!

278
00:14:52,424 --> 00:14:53,891
            [honking]

279
00:14:54,594 --> 00:14:56,527
    And you must do something
   about the garbage

280
00:14:56,629 --> 00:14:59,563
  piling up outside! The street
   sweepers are on strike

281
00:14:59,665 --> 00:15:02,432
     and the royal carpeters
      can't do their jobs!

282
00:15:02,756 --> 00:15:03,435
            [thunk]

283
00:15:03,536 --> 00:15:06,304
  Did you even know there were
   royal street carpeters?

284
00:15:06,406 --> 00:15:11,342
  Oh, dear. I do hope those
  aren't the <i>final</i> decorations

285
00:15:11,444 --> 00:15:12,277
   for the gala.

286
00:15:12,578 --> 00:15:13,554
   How rude!

287
00:15:13,779 --> 00:15:16,180
    Thank you for your
     constructive criticism.

288
00:15:16,282 --> 00:15:18,248
     But we don't really
     have time to chat so...

289
00:15:18,350 --> 00:15:19,116
          [door closes]

290
00:15:19,418 --> 00:15:23,721
        <i> ♪ [soft music] ♪</i>

291
00:15:23,823 --> 00:15:26,557
       Well, I hope <i>you're</i>
       enjoying yourself

292
00:15:26,659 --> 00:15:29,427
     on your super-relaxing
     picnic, sister.

293
00:15:30,229 --> 00:15:32,563
       I would be, if you
       hadn't made us hike

294
00:15:32,665 --> 00:15:34,799
        through a million
         PRICKLE BUSHES.

295
00:15:35,401 --> 00:15:36,067
             Agh!

296
00:15:36,169 --> 00:15:38,869
    Well, they hurt less than
     that horrible howling

297
00:15:38,971 --> 00:15:40,071
       you dragged us to.

298
00:15:40,173 --> 00:15:43,474
       That was Ponyliacci
       and it's an OPERA!

299
00:15:44,176 --> 00:15:45,509
         And you made us
          leave early,

300
00:15:45,611 --> 00:15:47,411
       even though it
       was still my turn!

301
00:15:47,613 --> 00:15:51,415
     Oh, just face it, Luna.
     You are NEVER happy.

302
00:15:51,617 --> 00:15:54,418
     Because you don't
      want me to be happy.

303
00:15:54,520 --> 00:15:56,487
        I always have to
       do things <i>your</i> way.

304
00:15:56,589 --> 00:15:57,722
       I bet you wish I'd
       never come back

305
00:15:57,824 --> 00:15:59,857
       so you could still
       rule day AND night!

306
00:15:59,959 --> 00:16:02,827
      You think I LIKE that
      kind of pressure?

307
00:16:02,929 --> 00:16:04,728
      Being responsible for
      every little thing

308
00:16:04,830 --> 00:16:06,731
      in Equestria AND you?

309
00:16:06,933 --> 00:16:09,867
       What I'd LIKE is a
     sister I can depend on!

310
00:16:09,969 --> 00:16:11,835
      YOU MEAN BOSS AROUND?!

311
00:16:12,037 --> 00:16:14,105
        CALM DOWN, LUNA!

312
00:16:14,207 --> 00:16:17,842
   No! And don't you dare use
   your Canterlot voice on me!

313
00:16:17,944 --> 00:16:19,477
     I think this adventure
     would be better

314
00:16:19,579 --> 00:16:21,446
     if I did it by MYSELF.

315
00:16:22,748 --> 00:16:25,215
     FINE! I just remembered
     something I forgot

316
00:16:25,317 --> 00:16:28,852
       I always wanted to
       do. Be! Alone!

317
00:16:30,356 --> 00:16:33,090
  Guess we have the same thing
   on both of our lists then.

318
00:16:36,997 --> 00:16:43,333
        <i> ♪ [busy music] ♪</i>

319
00:16:43,435 --> 00:16:45,870
       Pinkie! You got
      those appetizers yet?

320
00:16:46,672 --> 00:16:48,839
          Still mashing
         the guacamole!

321
00:16:49,541 --> 00:16:50,808
             Ah!

322
00:16:51,210 --> 00:16:53,177
So we're just going
have to do with sequins!

323
00:16:53,279 --> 00:16:55,479
          Um, sorry for
          the bad news,

324
00:16:55,581 --> 00:16:59,083
    but the courtyard is full
   of swans waiting to get in!

325
00:16:59,685 --> 00:17:00,718
            [honking]

326
00:17:00,820 --> 00:17:02,620
               And we're nowhere
                  near ready!

327
00:17:02,722 --> 00:17:04,688
       How do Celestia and
       Luna rule a kingdom

328
00:17:04,790 --> 00:17:07,758
    AND get all this done by
    themselves every year!?

329
00:17:07,860 --> 00:17:11,629
    Ha ha ha. Oh, how droll.

330
00:17:11,731 --> 00:17:13,964
      Uh, what's the funny
       part, exactly?

331
00:17:14,366 --> 00:17:16,733
     The princesses never do
    all the ceremony planning

332
00:17:16,835 --> 00:17:18,068
         by themselves.

333
00:17:18,370 --> 00:17:19,870
          They...don't?

334
00:17:20,172 --> 00:17:21,305
          Goodness, no!

335
00:17:21,407 --> 00:17:23,907
  That's what the gala
  planning committees are for.

336
00:17:24,009 --> 00:17:26,043
       Nopony could
        handle all <i>this</i>.

337
00:17:27,847 --> 00:17:30,147
      Are those...sequins?

338
00:17:30,849 --> 00:17:31,882
Still rude.

339
00:17:32,184 --> 00:17:36,620
    Ooh! New plan, everypony!
    We're going to delegate!

340
00:17:38,257 --> 00:17:39,890
    You! You're on food duty!

341
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:43,995
        I need gemstones...
        and purple satin!

342
00:17:44,797 --> 00:17:45,929
         Tell the ponies
          at the gates

343
00:17:46,031 --> 00:17:48,198
      that there's a slight
       delay on the gala!

344
00:17:48,300 --> 00:17:50,902
     Oh, um, if it's not too
      much trouble, I mean.

345
00:17:51,504 --> 00:17:54,238
   Uh. Now who can we get to
   clean up all this garbage?

346
00:17:54,340 --> 00:17:55,706
           [crashing]

347
00:17:56,108 --> 00:17:58,208
         I'm delegating!

348
00:17:58,310 --> 00:18:04,381
               ♪♪

349
00:18:04,483 --> 00:18:07,417
       So THIS is how you
       rule Equestria!

350
00:18:09,521 --> 00:18:11,388
           [slurping]

351
00:18:11,490 --> 00:18:13,957
       Ahh. Things are so
       much more relaxing

352
00:18:14,059 --> 00:18:16,026
    without my bossy sister.

353
00:18:16,128 --> 00:18:23,862
           [giggling]

354
00:18:24,837 --> 00:18:26,336
    Who needs a gloomy sister

355
00:18:26,438 --> 00:18:28,505
        moping around all
        the time anyway?

356
00:18:31,010 --> 00:18:31,742
              [pop]

357
00:18:32,444 --> 00:18:33,243
    [pop]

358
00:18:34,244 --> 00:18:35,022
   [snort]

359
00:18:35,147 --> 00:18:36,180
              Agh!

360
00:18:37,082 --> 00:18:40,250
   Honestly, princess. Didn't
   you wear <i>any</i> sunblock?

361
00:18:40,452 --> 00:18:43,987
    That's a thing? Celestia
     would have warned me...

362
00:18:44,089 --> 00:18:45,322
        if she were here.

363
00:18:48,895 --> 00:18:51,495
     [sigh] Now, was it two left
      turns and a right,

364
00:18:51,597 --> 00:18:53,465
        or two right
        turns and a left?

365
00:18:54,967 --> 00:18:56,933
       Luna always handled
       directions!

366
00:18:57,734 --> 00:18:58,413
           [crack]

367
00:18:58,538 --> 00:19:01,605
      <i> ♪ [horror sting] ♪</i>

368
00:19:01,707 --> 00:19:02,774
           [clucking]

369
00:19:03,376 --> 00:19:06,544
       <i> ♪ [heavy music] ♪</i>

370
00:19:06,846 --> 00:19:09,913
        [nervously] And scared away..
          the chickens!

371
00:19:15,254 --> 00:19:19,556
  Oh! I thought climbing Mt.
  Fillymanejaro was on MY list.

372
00:19:19,658 --> 00:19:22,993
  I'm not copying you. I just
  wanted to watch the sunrise.

373
00:19:23,295 --> 00:19:26,796
       Ah! I'm...here for
       the moonset.

374
00:19:28,233 --> 00:19:31,935
       So, uh, how did the
      rest of your day go?

375
00:19:32,137 --> 00:19:36,606
  Oh, amazing. Yeah. Fantastic.
    Best ever, really.

376
00:19:36,908 --> 00:19:39,109
         Yeah! Me... too...

377
00:19:41,080 --> 00:19:43,914
 You, you... can walk with me.
 You know, if you want, I mean.

378
00:19:44,016 --> 00:19:47,217
       Oh. Well. Since we're
       going the same way...

379
00:19:52,391 --> 00:19:56,727
  This is SO beautiful. It must
   be amazing in the sunlight.

380
00:19:57,129 --> 00:19:59,363
       The night's pretty
          special, too.

381
00:19:59,465 --> 00:20:04,334
               ♪♪

382
00:20:04,436 --> 00:20:05,770
           Lucky star!

383
00:20:06,772 --> 00:20:09,306
   You taught me to look for
   those when I was a filly.

384
00:20:09,408 --> 00:20:12,977
   [soft laugh] Hope I wasn't
   too <i>bossy</i> doing it.

385
00:20:13,879 --> 00:20:16,846
  You know, being with your
  sister all the time is hard but...

386
00:20:17,148 --> 00:20:20,184
     being without
     her? It's even harder.

387
00:20:20,586 --> 00:20:23,887
       I do know. And I
       wouldn't trade you

388
00:20:23,989 --> 00:20:26,423
     for any of the
     adventures on my list.

389
00:20:27,960 --> 00:20:29,292
     Not even your Zip-line?

390
00:20:29,962 --> 00:20:30,861
              [pop]

391
00:20:30,963 --> 00:20:32,863
      Not even my Zip-line.

392
00:20:33,165 --> 00:20:35,799
        I'm sorry I said
      those things before.

393
00:20:35,901 --> 00:20:39,236
   Sometimes it's just...tough
   being the little sister.

394
00:20:39,438 --> 00:20:42,940
   It's not always easy being
    the big sister, either.

395
00:20:43,042 --> 00:20:44,307
         I'm sorry too.

396
00:20:44,409 --> 00:20:50,514
               ♪♪

397
00:20:50,616 --> 00:20:54,652
   Oh! The sun and the moon
  together...at the same time!?

398
00:20:54,954 --> 00:20:57,855
        Now where have I
        seen THAT before?

399
00:20:58,957 --> 00:21:00,891
           [laughter]

400
00:21:00,993 --> 00:21:07,431
       <i> ♪ [bright music] ♪</i>

401
00:21:07,533 --> 00:21:09,533
      You think maybe
    Twilight's having trouble

402
00:21:09,635 --> 00:21:10,634
        with the amulet?

403
00:21:10,836 --> 00:21:12,169
       We should probably
         go help her.

404
00:21:14,573 --> 00:21:16,440
         OK, OK! I think
         I got it!

405
00:21:16,742 --> 00:21:19,543
  Sunburst says we just need to
   reset the amulet with this!

406
00:21:20,245 --> 00:21:21,478
   Turn the screw on the back...

407
00:21:21,591 --> 00:21:23,291
      [creak] [snap]

408
00:21:24,416 --> 00:21:26,551
 ...no more than one half turn..

409
00:21:27,953 --> 00:21:30,187
  Does anypony have some tape!?

